comes, and Expanding the Research Mandate -- tOnce Again Moving on Many Fronts -- tCrystallizing the Strengths of a Seventy-Year History -- tThe Influence of J.G. FitzGerald -- tConnections between FitzGerald and IHPME -- tThe Legacy of FitzGerald -- tOutcomes of the IHPME Approach -- tRange of Activity -- tInstitution-Building -- tIHPME and the University’s Role in the Twenty-First Century -- tUniversity-Based Policy Institutes -- tCommunication, Impact, Public Engagement -- tFinal Thoughts -- tOutcomes -- tConclusion -- tNotes -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aCanadians view their healthcare – recognized throughout the world as an exemplary system – as iconic and integral to their identity. In Toward the Health of a Nation Leslie Boehm recounts the first seventy years in the life of one of the foundations of Canada's healthcare system, the Institute of Health Policy, Management and Evaluation at the University of Toronto. Boehm – a graduate of IHPME, and an instructor there throughout his career – charts the institute's history from its inception in 1947 as the Department of Hospital Administration to the present day. The first program of its kind in Canada, and one of the few in the world, the school was founded at a time when the issue of healthcare was becoming a significant part of national and provincial discussions and policies. Initially concentrating on hospital management and professional degrees, it has expanded to offer academic degrees and facilitate important research into health systems, policies, and outcomes. In Toward the Health of a Nation Boehm demonstrates the excellence of the program, its faculty, and its graduates, as well as their accomplishments in major government initiatives and royal commissions. In the seventy years since IHPME's inception healthcare has grown to become a major part of government and business activity, and it will only increase in coming years. An in-depth history of a major program in graduate health education, Toward the Health of a Nation highlights how important healthcare is to a modern, functional society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGraduate studentsxEducationzOntariozTorontoxHistory. 0aMedical policyxStudy and teaching (Graduate)zOntariozTorontoxHistory. 0aPublic healthxStudy and teaching (Graduate)zOntariozTorontoxHistory. 7aMEDICAL / Health Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311127253508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2020z978311127473740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780228002284?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228002284423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228002284/original  a978-3-11-127253-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-127473-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles